article.description: — KJ Johnson and Jacari Lane each had 15 points and North Alabama beat Bellarmine 70-57 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Johnson puts up 15 as North Alabama beats Bellarmine 70-57
article.linkText: Johnson puts up 15 as North Alabama beats Bellarmine 70-57
article.story:
LOUISVILLE, Ky. -- — KJ Johnson and Jacari Lane each had 15 points and North Alabama beat Bellarmine 70-57 on Thursday night.

Johnson added six assists for the Lions (17-11, 9-6 Atlantic Sun Conference). Will Soucie finished 5 of 6 from the field to finish with 12 points.

Peter Suder led the Knights (12-16, 7-8) in scoring, finishing with 17 points and three steals. Ben Johnson added nine points for Bellarmine. Landin Hacker also had eight points.

------
